  "prompt": "DiD the members of indian constituent assembly help J&k in making of their constitution?",
  "response": "The Indian Constituent Assembly, which was responsible for drafting the Constitution of India, did not play a direct role in the creation of the Constitution of Jammu and Kashmir. Jammu and Kashmir had its own Constituent Assembly, which was elected to draft and adopt a separate constitution for the state.\n\nThe Constitution of Jammu and Kashmir was adopted on November 17, 1956, and came into effect on January 26, 1957. This separate constitution granted the state a special autonomous status under Article 370 of the Indian Constitution, allowing it to have its own laws and regulations to a significant extent.\n\nThus, while the Indian Constituent Assembly provided the broader framework of governance through the Indian Constitution, the Constitution of Jammu and Kashmir was formulated independently by the J&K Constituent Assembly.",
